title: Uruguay Manufacturing Production
description: Industrial Production in Uruguay increased 2.70 percent in September of 2022 over the same month in the previous year. Industrial Production in Uruguay averaged 4.69 percent from 2003 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 57.25 percent in October of 2003 and a record low of -31.14 percent in January of 2003. In Uruguay, industrial production measures the output of businesses integrated in the manufacturing sector of the economy. This page provides - Uruguay Industrial Production - actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: Instituto Nacional de Estadística, Uruguay
